-- New South Wales Will Retain Ownership of Cobbora Coal Mine, Review Reports
-- B y   R e b e c c a   K e e n a n
-- 2010-10-10T19:56:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-10/new-south-wales-will-retain-ownership-of-cobbora-coal-mine-review-reports.html
Australia’s New South Wales state
will retain ownership of the A$1.3 billion Cobbora power coal
mine to secure supply for its electricity generation, the
Australian Financial Review reported, citing the government.  New South Wales was considering selling the mine, the
newspaper said, citing a statement from the state’s Electricity
Reform Project Office.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rebecca Keenan in Melbourne at 
